<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Shoen Obituary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- The Associated Press erroneously reported Oct.  
5, in an obituary about U-Haul International Inc. founder Leonard 
S. Shoen, that the company filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy 
protection as a result of a 1995 court judgment. 
</P>
<P>
	In fact, neither Phoenix-based U-Haul International Inc. nor its  
holding company, Reno, Nev.-based Amerco Inc., filed for bankruptcy 
protection. Five directors of Amerco Inc. sought personal 
bankruptcy protection after they were ordered to pay a $461 million 
judgment stemming from an family battle over control of the 
company. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
