<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Heisman Hopeful Warrick Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Florida State receiver and Heisman  
hopeful Peter Warrick was arrested today on grand theft charges 
stemming from an alleged theft at a department store. 
</P>
<P>
	Also arrested on grand theft charges was Seminoles receiver and  
Warrick's roommate Laveranues Coles. 
</P>
<P>
	Both players were suspended from Saturday's game against Miami  
and could be suspended for the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this week, the players said they were cooperating with  
police. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not like we grabbed clothes and ran out,'' Coles said  
Tuesday. ``It's not like that at all. They wanted to question us 
about some things. We went and answered some questions and that's 
it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Warrick sounded confident that he and Coles would be cleared of  
any wrongdoing. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not like I killed the president,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	Coles and Warrick were arrested in 1998 in separate incidents.  
</P>
<P>
	Coles was charged with simple battery, a misdemeanor, in a  
domestic incident when he allegedly struck his stepmother outside 
her home. He was suspended for last year's opener against Texas A&AMP;M 
and later served 150 hours of community service. He also was 
suspended for this year's opener for academic reasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Warrick was charged with disorderly conduct and resisting  
arrest, both misdemeanors, for an altercation in the parking lot of 
a Tampa fast-food restaurant. The charges were eventually dropped. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
