<HEADLINE> Devils Acquire Center Steve Kelly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- The New Jersey Devils have acquired  
center Steve Kelly from the Tampa Bay Lightning for a seventh-round 
draft pick in the 2000 entry draft, the team announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kelly, 22, joined the Devils from the IHL's Detroit Vipers. He  
was Edmonton's first choice and the sixth overall selection in the 
1995 draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Kelly, a 6-foot-1, 190-pounder, split the 1998-99 season between  
Tampa Bay and Cleveland of the IHL. In his four seasons in the NHL 
he had four goals and six assists for 10 points, and 56 penalty 
minutes in 85 games played for Edmonton and Tampa Bay. 
  	   	
</P>
