<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
	Southwest Airlines, up 1 1/16 at 17 15/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Dallas-based airline said its planes were more crowded in  
September, and Deutsche Bank upgraded its earnings outlook on the 
company. 

</P>
<P>
	Barnes &AMP; Noble Inc., down 2 5/8 at 23 7/8  
</P>
<P>
	The New York-based bookstore chain, in a bid to expand its  
computer software and video game offerings, is buying Babbage's 
Etc. for $189 million in cash. J.P. Morgan responds by cutting its 
earnings outlook for the company. 

</P>
<P>
	Aetna Inc., up 1/4 at 52 3/4  
</P>
<P>
	A Philadelphia law firm filed suit against Aetna's U.S.  
Healthcare unit, accusing the health insurer of withholding vital 
information from members. The suit is the second of an expected 
wave of class-actions suits against health-maintenance 
organizations 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
	Trend Micro, up 4 3/4 at 20 1/2  
</P>
<P>
	The Tokyo-based maker of anti-virus computer software will  
provide MCI Worldcom with its anti-virus technology. 

</P>
<P>
	ESPS Inc., down 2 1/8 at 6 1/8  
</P>
<P>
	The Fort Washington, Pa.-based developer of electronic  
compliance systems says it won't meet earning estimates due to slow 
sales of its new products partly as a result of Y2K concerns. 

</P>
<P>
	Zomax Optical Media, up 3 9/16 at 35 1/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Minneapolis-based providers of services to software  
publishers said it will beat earnings forecasts because of 
production improvements. 




  	   	
