<HEADLINE> U.S. Grand Prix Planned for Indy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- Motor racing's world governing body made it  
official Thursday -- Formula One will return to the United States 
with a race next Sept. 24 at Indianapolis Motor Speedway 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Grand Prix, the first F1 event in the U.S. since 1991,  
was on the race schedule released by FIA's World Motor Sports 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
	The 2000 F1 season will open with the Australian Grand Prix in  
Melbourne on March 12, followed by the Brazilian Grand Prix in Sao 
Paulo on March 26. 
</P>
<P>
	Also confirmed were: Monaco, June 4;, Canada, June 18; Germany,  
July 30; Hungary, Aug. 13; Belgium, Aug. 27; Italy, Sept. 10; 
Japan, Oct. 8; and Malaysia, Oct. 22. 
</P>
<P>
	Dates for the Austrian, British, European, French, San Marino  
and Spanish races will be announced within the next three weeks. 
  	   	
</P>
