<HEADLINE> Allison's Wrist Injury Worsens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OTTAWA (AP) -- Boston Bruins forward Jason Allison has torn  
cartilage in his wrist, and he could need surgery if it continues 
to worsen. 
</P>
<P>
	Allison, who played in Thursday night's 4-3 loss to the Ottawa  
Senators, said one doctor told him to rest, while another told him 
he needed surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	``There are all kinds of tears in the muscle,'' he said  
Wednesday, a day after an MRI revealed the damage. ``There are 
different options. If it gets better, I can play with it and rest 
it on the off days. If it doesn't, I'll have to take a little time 
off to get the swelling down.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Allison, who will continue to play for now, said the injury  
worsened when he took faceoffs on opening night against Carolina on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've been battling on faceoffs,'' he said Thursday.  
``(Faceoffs) are something I have to make my game better. I have to 
get a little stronger.'' 
  	   	
