<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Coelho Wall Free of Donors' Names </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- While raising money for a Portuguese-American  
memorial wall in connection with a 1998 world's fair in Lisbon, Al 
Gore's campaign chairman, Tony Coelho, said contributors' names 
would be engraved on the monument. 
</P>
<P>
	The only names now on the 8-by-60-foot sculpture, ``The Wave,''  
are those of the artists, according to a check by The Associated 
Press in Lisbon. 
</P>
<P>
	Coelho, as commissioner general for the U.S. pavilion at Expo 98  
in Lisbon, took out a $300,000 personal loan to get the sculpture 
built, and formed the Luso-American Wave Foundation to repay the 
costs. 
</P>
<P>
	The State Department inspector general, in a report made public  
last weekend, said the pavilion's books carried the costs of the 
sculpture as a liability, and taxpayers could be responsible for 
any unpaid bills. The report also cited mismanagement of the 
pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
	Coelho's attorney, Stanley Brand, said Thursday that the names  
would be engraved on the wall, but he did not know when. He said 
Coelho this week repaid the outstanding balance of more than 
$119,000 on the loan. 
</P>
<P>
	Brand said he did not have precise figures on how much of the  
loan was raised from donors other than Coelho, but estimated the 
figure was $150,000 to $200,000. 
</P>
<P>
	The sculpture, in the shape of a wave, is a memorial to honor  
the contributions of Portuguese who emigrated to the United States. 
Coelho is a Portuguese-American. 
</P>
<P>
	The expo's Internet site said, ``Contribute to The Wave and have  
your name engraved on the monument.'' The notice also said a family 
name could be included. 
</P>
<P>
	The Luso-American Wave Foundation's certificate to operate and  
its articles of incorporation were revoked Sept. 7 by the District 
of Columbia government, ``for having failed and/or refused to file 
reports and pay all fees due and owing on or before April 15, 1999 
and 1998.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
