<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Falcons To Start Backup QB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The Atlanta Falcons will start backup quarterback  
Tony Graziani on Sunday at New Orleans as the team waits for Chris 
Chandler's injured hamstring to heal. 
</P>
<P>
	Chandler had a limited practice Thursday, but a team spokesman  
said Chandler likely will not be able to play against the Saints 
(1-2). He is listed as doubtful. 
</P>
<P>
	Graziani, who suffered a concussion last week against Baltimore,  
was taken off the injury list Thursday. The start Sunday will be 
his second in a row and third in the last four games. 
</P>
<P>
	Chandler injured his hamstring in a season-opening loss to  
Minnesota. After missing the next game, he aggravated the injury in 
the third game of the season against St. Louis. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
