<HEADLINE> Historic Group Honors Payton, Others </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Football legend Walter Payton, Sen. Daniel  
Patrick Moynihan and Boston Mayor Thomas M. Menino are among 
winners of this year's National Preservation Awards. The list of 
the 20 honorees was released today. 
</P>
<P>
	The winning organizations, groups and citizens will be honored  
Oct. 22 in Washington at 50-year anniversary conference of the 
National Trust for Historic Preservation. 
</P>
<P>
	``This year's National Preservation Award winners have shown  
ingenuity, tenacity and diversity in their preservation 
initiatives,'' National Trust president Richard Moe said. 
</P>
<P>
	The organization praised Payton, the former Chicago Bears  
running back, for his work to preserve the historic railroad 
roundhouse in Aurora, Ill. It is the oldest standing limestone 
roundhouse in the country, and harbors a brewpub as well as a 
museum today. 
</P>
<P>
	Moynihan, D-N.Y., received the award for his ``lifelong  
commitment to preservation,'' said the organization, and Menino was 
lauded for his urban Main Street redevelopment program. The program 
led to the creation of more than 2,000 new jobs in 280 businesses 
and 100 restored storefronts in Boston, the trust said. 
</P>
<P>
	The other winners were:  
</P>
<P>
	-- Grand Central Terminal restoration team, New York City.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Galveston historical Foundation, Texas.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Stratford Hall Plantation, Va.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Belle Shore Apartment Hotel, Chicago.  
</P>
<P>
	-- The Boston Custom House, Boston.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Edith Bingham, Frankfort, Ky.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Buffalo Historical Society, Buffalo, N.D.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Willbar M. Feltner, chairman of F&AMP;M Bank, Winchester, Va.  
</P>
<P>
	-- General Services Administration, National Capital Region.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Historic Restoration Inc., New Orleans.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Idaho Heritage Trust, Boise, Idaho.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Jeanne Jackson, Banana Republic CEO and president, New York  
City. 
</P>
<P>
	-- San Francisco City Hall, San Francisco.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Maryland Department of Natural Resources -- program Open Space  
and Rural Legacy 
</P>
<P>
	-- Salve Regina University, Newport, R.I.  
</P>
<P>
	-- Ralph Sr. and Sunny Wilson House, Temple, Texas.  
</P>
<P>
	-- University of Washington-Tacoma.  
  	   	
</P>
