<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Police Arrest Muslim Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOSCOW (AP) -- Police have arrested a Muslim leader who is  
accused of storming a government building in the southern region of 
Dagestan more than a year ago, Russia's prime minister said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Nadir Khachilayev was arrested late Wednesday, Prime Minister  
Vladimir Putin said in comments picked up by the Interfax news 
agency. 
</P>
<P>
	Khachilayev has been wanted since 1998, when several hundred  
supporters held policemen and officials hostage at the government 
building in Dagestan's capital, Makhachkala. He and his brother 
were accused of organizing the raid, during which three policemen 
were killed. 
</P>
<P>
	The brother, Magomed Khachilayev, leads an organization  
representing an ethnic minority in Dagestan, the Laks. He was 
arrested in Dagestan's capital, Makhachkala, several months after 
the raid, but Nadir Khachilayev escaped. 
</P>
<P>
	Putin did not say where Khachilayev had been found. Interfax  
said that as recently as August he had been in the Dagestani 
village of Karamakhi, the site of fighting between government 
troops and Islamic militants in late August and September. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
