	Davis, an environmental activist, alleges that Ventura used his  
position to make money from his autobiography and from his August 
return to the professional wrestling ring as a referee. Those 
ventures could bring Ventura as much as $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
	If the 25 signatures Davis gathered so far can be verified, the  
state Supreme Court could order a public hearing. 
</P>
<P>
	If the court decides there is enough evidence supporting the  
allegations, then the secretary of state issues a full recall 
petition. That petition would require 500,000 signatures to trigger 
a special recall election. 
  	   	
