<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Harbaugh Expected To Face Lions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- San Diego Chargers quarterback Jim Harbaugh,  
nursing two cracked ribs and a bruised throwing elbow, practiced 
Thursday and is expected to play in Sunday's game at Detroit. 
</P>
<P>
	``I feel probably better than I expected,'' said Harbaugh, who  
didn't practice on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Some other Chargers aren't feeling so well.  
</P>
<P>
	Left tackle John Jackson isn't expected to play because of a  
back injury and wide receiver Mikhael Ricks, the team's emergency 
quarterback, and cornerback Terrance Shaw were downgraded from 
questionable to doubtful. Ricks hurt his neck while running a 
reverse in Sunday's 21-14 win over Kansas City and Shaw missed the 
game with a sprained ankle sustained the week before. 
</P>
<P>
	There are other injuries the team has to monitor prior to  
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're on the edge with quite a few people here and we're going  
to have to make some last-minute decisions on who plays,'' coach 
Mike Riley said. ``So we'll probably take most everybody with us 
and figure out the last few healthy ones while we're there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Running back Natrone Means, still hobbled by knee and ankle  
injuries sustained in the opener, didn't practice, but is expected 
to play. Means had 14 carries Sunday for 26 yards and is averaging 
just 2.7 yards per carry after three games. 
</P>
<P>
	Riley was encouraged with Harbaugh's workout. Harbaugh was held  
out of Wednesday's practice, although he threw some passes on the 
side. He was hurt in the first quarter last Sunday, and Erik Kramer 
came in and threw two touchdown passes. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was great to see Jim work today,'' Riley said. ``I don't  
think he was 100 percent, but he actually got quite a few reps. We 
obviously need both of those guys ready to go. 
</P>
<P>
	``At this point, I would say everything is status quo with Jim  
as our starter,'' said Riley, who added he won't make a final 
decision until Friday or Saturday, after talking with Harbaugh and 
the trainer. 
</P>
<P>
	Raleigh Roundtree is expected to start in place of Jackson, who  
had made 51 straight starts. Roundtree started the first three 
games at right guard, then moved to left tackle after Jackson got 
hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	Depth is a big concern on the offensive line for a team that has  
allowed nine sacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
