<HEADLINE> Raptors' GM Gets Contract Extension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- The Toronto Raptors gave general manager Glen  
Grunwald a four-year contract extension Thursday that will run 
through the 2003-04 season. 
</P>
<P>
	The Chicago lawyer has orchestrated the Raptors' rise from a  
lowly expansion team to aspiring playoff contender. 
</P>
<P>
	Both Grunwald and coach Butch Carter were entering the final  
year of their contracts. The Raptors are expected to announce a 
contract extension for Carter shortly. 
</P>
<P>
	Grunwald has been with the team since 1994, a year before the  
team played its first NBA game. He was brought into the 
organization by Isiah Thomas, the Raptors' former GM and part 
owner. 
</P>
<P>
	He took over as general manager in November 1997 after Thomas  
left the club over a dispute with former partner Allan Slaight. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
