<HEADLINE> Former Bears DB Whitsell Dead at 63 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Dave Whitsell, a defensive back on the  
Chicago Bears' 1963 NFL championship team, died Thursday after 
battling prostate cancer. He was 63. 
</P>
<P>
	Whitsell played collegiately at Indiana. He was with the Bears  
from 1961-66 and was a member of the 1963 team that beat the New 
York Giants 14-10 for the title. He later played with the New 
Orleans Saints from 1967-69. 
</P>
<P>
	He died early Thursday at the Kenner Regional Medical Center in  
Kenner, La. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
