<HEADLINE> AP Names Petty To Oregon Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Terrence Petty, correspondent in charge of  
The Associated Press bureau in Providence, R.I., has been named 
news editor in Portland. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Portland Chief of Bureau  
Elaine Hooker. 
</P>
<P>
	Petty joined the AP in Albany in 1982 after working for three  
New York newspapers: the Plattsburgh Press-Republican, the Syracuse 
Post-Standard and Herald-Journal and the Albany Times Union. 
</P>
<P>
	He worked on the International Desk at AP's New York  
headquarters for two years before being assigned to Bonn, Germany, 
in 1987. He returned to the United States 10 years later as 
Providence correspondent. 
</P>
<P>
	Petty, 48, is a native of Rutland, Vt., and a graduate of the  
University of Vermont. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
