<HEADLINE> Macromedia To Acquire Andromedia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Macromedia Inc., a provider of tools for  
building Web sites, said Thursday it is acquiring Andromedia Inc., 
maker of electronic commerce software for the Internet. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement was made in New York at the Fall Internet World  
'99 convention. 
</P>
<P>
	Andromedia, based in San Francisco, makes software that analyzes  
data about Web site visitors. It also allows Web sites to be 
customized based on the data about the user. Terms of the deal were 
not announced. 
</P>
<P>
	The purchase is part of Macromedia's strategy announced Thursday  
to integrate its Web authoring software with that of Andromedia's 
and several other companies. Macromedia said its ``ebusiness 
infrastructure'' strategy will include alliances with BroadVision 
Inc. and USWeb/CKS. 
</P>
<P>
	The new infrastructure delivers solutions for each step of the  
Web content lifecycle, Macromedia said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Macromedia, based in San Francisco, makes Dreamweaver, a Web  
site authoring software and the Shockwave player, a popular media 
playback device for Web content, including games, business 
presentations, and advertisements. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
