<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European shares closed higher Thursday, after the  
European Central Bank decided to leave its key interest rates 
unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
	Bank President Wim Duisenberg said more evidence of inflation is  
needed to justify an interest rate rise. The bank left its main 
refinancing rate at 2.5 percent, where it has been since a 0.5 
percent cut in April. It also confirmed Thursday that its overnight 
deposit rate will remain at 1.5 percent and its marginal lending 
rate will continue to be 3.5 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 614 European companies rose 2.64  
points, or 0.9 percent, to close at 311.57. The best performing 
sector was telecommunications, up 2.3 percent, with MCI WorldCom's 
bid for Sprint earlier this week fueling talk about consolidation 
across Europe. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, telecom shares were the best performers in the FTSE  
100 index of blue-chip shares, which closed with a gain of 1.7 
percent, at 6,200.4. 
</P>
<P>
	Orange led, closing up 88 pence at 1,312 pence; Energis rose 112  
pence to 1,771 pence; Telewest Communications rose 14.25 pence to 
236 pence; and Colt Telecom rose 98 pence to 1,668 pence. 
</P>
<P>
	London shares were also buoyed by the Bank of England's decision  
to leave its main lending rate unchanged at 5.25 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 310 companies in  
countries that joined the single currency, closed up 2.46 points at 
327.78. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 32.45 points to 3785.24,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed up 36.22 points at 3738.93. 
</P>
<P>
	In domestic markets, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index rose 1.2  
percent to 5,419.31, the Paris CAC-40 index rose 1.1 percent to 
4,742.26, Amsterdam's AEX index rose 0.2 percent to 555.77 and 
Milan's MIBtel index rose 0.2 percent to 34,089.00. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
