	CINCINNATI (AP) -- A judge's dismissal of Cincinnati's lawsuit  
against the firearms industry will be used to try and defeat 
similar lawsuits across the country, a lawyer for gun makers said 
today. In the first dismissal of such a case, Hamilton County 
Common Pleas Judge Robert Ruehlman said the city's claims were 
vague and unsupported by legal precedent. ``It very clearly points 
out the weaknesses in the other cities' suits,'' said Jim Dorr, a 
Chicago lawyer for gun makers Sturm, Ruger &AMP; Co. Inc., of 
Southport, Conn., and Smith &AMP; Wesson Corp., of Springfield, Mass. 
Cincinnati intends to appeal the decision within a few days, said 
Stanley M. Chesley, the city's lawyer. 

</P>
