<HEADLINE> Diabetic Hiker Found Dead in Mtns. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- A diabetic man who didn't return after a  
weekend hike in the San Gabriel Mountains was found dead Wednesday, 
his dog by his side. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheriff's deputies searching Angeles National Forest found the  
body of Tadeo Yanez, 26, of Commerce in a trail camp about nine 
miles from where he left his sport utility vehicle Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	His mother reported him missing Monday morning.  
</P>
<P>
	She said Yanez usually injected himself with insulin when he  
started a hike, and authorities said a used syringe was found in 
his vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles County Sheriff's Detective Joe Martinez said it  
appeared that Yanez struggled for a while at the place where he 
fell and then succumbed. 
</P>
<P>
	``There are some scratch marks on the body that would indicate  
the dog was attempting to revive or at least awaken the master,'' 
Martinez said. 
</P>
<P>
	The dog, Lobo, was still at Yanez's side when searchers found  
him. 
</P>
