<HEADLINE> Sept., Year-To-Date Retail Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	September sales and sales for the fiscal year to date reported  
by leading retailers. 
</P>
<P>
	The sales compare the current year's sales with those of the  
previous year. Retailers are ranked according to results at the end 
of September. 
</P>
<P>
	Reporting periods vary slightly. Most retailers' fiscal years  
end in late January or early February. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales include those from stores open at least a year, also known  
as same-store or comparable store sales, and total sales. Retailers 
release only percentage changes for same-store sales, while they 
provide dollar figures and percentages for total sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Securities analysts and investors believe same-store sales  
provide a more accurate assessment of a retailer's performance than 
total sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wal-Mart Stores Inc.  
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended Oct. 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 7.2 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $15.66 billion, up 26.4 percent from $12.38  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Eight months ended Oct. 1: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 8.2 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $102.28 billion, up 18.2 percent from $86.52  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Sears, Roebuck and Co.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended Oct. 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 4.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.63 billion, flat with a year ago.  
</P>
<P>
 *Eight months ended Oct. 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 1.4 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $25.58 billion, down 2.8 percent from $26.31  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Kmart Corp.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended Sept. 29: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 2.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.99 billion, up 4.5 percent from $2.86  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Eight months ended Sept. 29: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 5.4 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $22.34 billion, up 7.3 percent from $20.89  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *J.C. Penney Co. Inc.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended Oct. 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.1 percent at Penney stores only.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $2.88 billion, up 8.4 percent from $2.66  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Eight months ended Oct. 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales fell 0.3 percent at Penney stores only.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $20.29 billion, up 7.5 percent from $18.88  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
