<HEADLINE> Al Franken Working on Screenplay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ERIE, Pa. (AP) -- Al Franken is no big fat idiot. He's a serious  
screenwriter. 
</P>
<P>
	The former ``Saturday Night Life'' writer and performer and  
author of the book ``Rush Limbaugh Is a Big Fat Idiot'' is working 
on a dramatic screenplay about small-town life in Minnesota, where 
he grew up. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want to be taken seriously if I feel like I know what I'm  
talking about,'' Franken said Wednesday before a speech at Penn 
State's campus in Erie. 
</P>
<P>
	Franken has taken on serious themes before: He wrote the  
screenplay to ``When a Man Loves A Woman,'' in which Meg Ryan 
played an alcoholic. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
